  string
  line `[Rules of procedure of the Legislative Assembly of the new State.] Rep. by the Adaptation of`
  line `laws (No. 3) Order, 1956.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (48307)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Court of the Judicial Commissioner for the new State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314&sectionId=48307&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `As from the commencement of`
  line `this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Courts of the Judicial Commissioner for the existing States (hereafter in this`
  line `Part referred to as "the existing Courts") shall be amalgamated and shall constitute the Court of`
  line `the Judicial Commissioner for the new State (hereafter in this Part referred to as "the new Court");`
  line
  line `(b) the Judicial Commissioner and the Additional Judicial Commissioner, if any, for the`
  line `existing State of Himachal Pradesh shall be respectively the Judicial Commissioner and the`
  line `Additional Judicial Commissioner for the new State;`
  line
  line `(c) every person who immediately before the commencement of this Act, is an officer or`
  line `servant of either of the existing Courts shall be an officer or servant, as the case may be, of the`
  line `new Court deemed to have been appointed on the same terms and conditions of service (or on`
  line `terms and conditions as similar thereto as the changes effected by this Act permit) as were`
  line `applicable to him immediately before such commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this clause shall be deemed to prevent the new Court from`
  line `altering the designation or the duties of any office or post;`
  line
  line `(d) the new Court shall have all such original, appellate and other jurisdiction as under any`
  line `law is exercisable immediately before the commencement of this Act by either of the existing`
  line `Courts in respect of any area forming part of the new State;`
  line
  line `(e) the new Court shall have the same powers to admit, suspend and remove advocates, vakils`
  line `and pleaders and to make rules with respect to advocates, vakils and pleaders in the whole of the`
  line `new State as are immediately before the commencement of this Act, exercisable by either of the`
  line `existing Courts:`
  line
  line `Provided that subject to any rules made by the new Court in exercise of the powers conferred`
  line `by this clause, any person who immediately before the commencement of this Act is an advocate,`
  line `vakil or pleader entitled to practise in either of the existing Courts shall be recognised as an`
  line `advocate, vakil or pleader entitled to practise in the new Court;`
  line
  line `(f) subject to the provisions of this Part, the law in force immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act with respect to the practice and procedure in the Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner for the existing State of Himachal Pradesh shall, until varied or altered by a`
  line `competent authority, apply in relation to the new Court with such modifications as may be made`
  line `by that Court;`
  line
  line `(g) the Judicial Commissioners' Courts (Declaration as High Courts) Act, 1950 (15 of 1950)`
  line `shall apply to the new Court as if the new Court were in existence at the commencement of that`
  line `Act; and any other law in force immediately before the commencement of this Act relating to`
  line `appeals to the Supreme Court from the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for the existing State`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh shall, with necessary modifications, apply in relation to the new Court;`
  line
  line `(h) all proceedings which immediately before the commencement of this Act are pending in`
  line `either of the existing Courts shall by virtue of this Act stand transferred to the new Court and shall`
  line `be continued as if they had been proceedings instituted in that Court;`
  line
  line `(i) any order made by either of the existing Courts in any such proceedings as aforesaid shall`
  line `for all purposes have effect, not only as an order of that Court, but also as an order made by the`
  line `new Court;`
  line
  line `(j) references in any law to either of the existing Courts by whatever name, shall, unless the`
  line `context otherwise requires, be construed as references to the new Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (48308)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Subordinate Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314&sectionId=48308&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `All Courts which immediately before the commencement of this Act`
  line `were exercising lawful powers, authority and jurisdiction under the superintendence and control of`
  line `either of the existing Courts in any area forming part of the new State shall, until further provision is`
  line `made by a competent legislature or authority, continue to exercise their respective powers, authority`
  line `and jurisdiction in that area under the superintendence and control of the new Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (48309)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Existing authorities and officers to continue to function in the new State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314&sectionId=48309&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line Save
  line `asotherwise provided in this Act, all authorities and all officers, judicial, executive and ministerial,`
  line `who immediately before the commencement of this Act were exercising lawful functions in any area`
  line `forming part of the new State, shall, until further provision is made by a competent authority, continue`
  line `to exercise their respective functions as far as may be, in the same manner and to the same extent as`
  line `they were doing before such commencement.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (48310)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Existing laws to continue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314&sectionId=48310&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all the law in force`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act in any area forming part of the new State shall`
  line `continue to be in force until repealed or amended by a competent legislature or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (48311)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314&sectionId=48311&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the`
  line `new State of any law made before the commencement of this Act, any Court, tribunal or authority`
  line `may, subject to any express provision of this Act, construe the law with such alterations not affecting`
  line `the substance as may be necessary or proper to adapt it to the matter before the Court, tribunal or`
  line `authority, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (48312)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Existing taxes to continue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314&sectionId=48312&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `All taxes, duties, cesses and fees which immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act were being lawfully levied in either of the existing States or any part`
  line `thereof, shall continue to be levied in the same manner and to the same extent and to be applied for`
  line `the same purposes until other provision is made by a competent legislature or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (48313)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Saving of the powers of the Central Government in relation to the Bhakra-Nangal Project.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314&sectionId=48313&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall be deemed to derogate from the powers of the Central`
  line `Government to make such arrangements or to take such action in relation to the Bhakra-Nangal`
  line `Project as may, having due regard to the purposes of the Project, be necessary to ensure its proper`
  line `administration and effective implementation.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (48314)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314&sectionId=48314&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00023_195432_1517807321314
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may make such orders not inconsistent with the said provisions, as appears to`
  line `him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such power shall be exercised by the President after the expiry of one year from`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `हिमाचल प्रदेश और बिलासपुर (नया राज्‍य) अधिनियम,1954`
